{
  "info": {
    "name": "BayFormFlow — auth (local)",
    "_postman_id": "b0f1a1c2-0000-4a00-9000-bayformflowauth",
    "description": "Kit de teste manual da Edge Function `auth` no Supabase local.\n\nRotas: POST /functions/v1/auth/operators e POST /functions/v1/auth/companies.\n\nSubida do ambiente (volume limpo, nesta ordem):\n1) npx supabase db start — sobe SÓ o Postgres (evita o 503 do PostgREST em banco novo).\n2) Flyway: docker compose -f setup/docker/docker-compose.local.yaml run --rm local_flyway migrate — aplica V001–V010; a V010 JÁ cria o admin (não existe mais seed.sql).\n3) npx supabase start — demais serviços; os schemas já existem e o health check passa.\n\nAntes de rodar: preencha a variável `anonKey` com a anon/publishable key impressa pelo `supabase start`. Rode o request 1 (Login) primeiro — ele salva `adminToken` automaticamente.\n\nObs.: os CHECKs do banco (CNPJ com dígito verificador, phonenumber) podem rejeitar valores que o Zod aceita — nesse caso a saga retorna 500 (rollback). Os samples usam valores que passam.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://127.0.0.1:54321" },
    { "key": "anonKey", "value": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZS1kZW1vIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJleHAiOjE5ODM4MTI5OTZ9.CRXP1A7WOeoJeXxjNni43kdQwgnWNReilDMblYTn_I0" },
    { "key": "adminEmail", "value": "admin@bayformflow.local" },
    { "key": "adminPassword", "value": "Admin@12345" },
    { "key": "adminToken", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Login admin (salva adminToken)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "if (json.access_token) { pm.collectionVariables.set('adminToken', json.access_token); }",
              "pm.test('200 + access_token', function () {",
              "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "  pm.expect(json.access_token, 'access_token').to.be.a('string');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "apikey", "value": "{{anonKey}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/v1/token?grant_type=password",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "v1", "token"],
          "query": [{ "key": "grant_type", "value": "password" }]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{adminEmail}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{adminPassword}}\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "signInWithPassword direto no Auth (NÃO passa pela Edge Function). Salva o access_token do admin em {{adminToken}}."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Whoami — rpc me() (confirma is_admin)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('200 + is_admin true', function () {",
              "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "  const j = pm.response.json();",
              "  pm.expect(j.is_admin, 'is_admin').to.eql(true);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "apikey", "value": "{{anonKey}}" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
          { "key": "Content-Profile", "value": "helpers" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/rest/v1/rpc/me",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["rest", "v1", "rpc", "me"]
        },
        "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" },
        "description": "Sanidade: confirma que o token é de um admin (a Edge Function exige isso; senão retorna 403). A me() vive no schema helpers — o header Content-Profile diz ao PostgREST onde procurar (sem ele: PGRST202, pois o default é public)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Provisionar operador (201)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('201 + user_id/employee_id', function () {",
              "  pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
              "  const j = pm.response.json();",
              "  pm.expect(j).to.have.property('user_id');",
              "  pm.expect(j).to.have.property('employee_id');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "apikey", "value": "{{anonKey}}" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/functions/v1/auth/operators",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["functions", "v1", "auth", "operators"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"display_name\": \"Fulano De Tal\",\n  \"email\": \"operador@bayformflow.local\",\n  \"password\": \"Senha12345\",\n  \"position\": \"Validador\",\n  \"is_admin\": false\n}"
        },
        "description": "Cadastro de operador. Troque o email a cada execução (email repetido -> 409)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Provisionar compania (201)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('201 + user_id/company_id', function () {",
              "  pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
              "  const j = pm.response.json();",
              "  pm.expect(j).to.have.property('user_id');",
              "  pm.expect(j).to.have.property('company_id');",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "apikey", "value": "{{anonKey}}" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/functions/v1/auth/companies",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["functions", "v1", "auth", "companies"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"display_name\": \"Empresa Modelo\",\n  \"email\": \"empresa@bayformflow.local\",\n  \"password\": \"Senha12345\",\n  \"cnpj\": \"11222333000181\",\n  \"phonenumber\": \"11987654321\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "Cadastro de compania. CNPJ 11222333000181 tem dígito verificador válido. Troque o email a cada execução."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Operador sem token (401)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": ["pm.test('401', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(401); });"]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "apikey", "value": "{{anonKey}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/functions/v1/auth/operators",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["functions", "v1", "auth", "operators"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"display_name\": \"Fulano De Tal\",\n  \"email\": \"x@bayformflow.local\",\n  \"password\": \"Senha12345\",\n  \"position\": \"Validador\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "Sem header Authorization -> 401 (middleware requireAuth, antes do Zod)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Operador body inválido (400)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": ["pm.test('400', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(400); });"]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "apikey", "value": "{{anonKey}}" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/functions/v1/auth/operators",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["functions", "v1", "auth", "operators"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"nao-eh-email\",\n  \"password\": \"123\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "Body inválido (faltam campos, email/senha ruins) -> 400 (zValidator/Zod)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "7. Validador com is_admin (400 refine)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": ["pm.test('400 (refine)', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(400); });"]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "apikey", "value": "{{anonKey}}" },
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/functions/v1/auth/operators",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["functions", "v1", "auth", "operators"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"display_name\": \"Fulano De Tal\",\n  \"email\": \"refine@bayformflow.local\",\n  \"password\": \"Senha12345\",\n  \"position\": \"Validador\",\n  \"is_admin\": true\n}"
        },
        "description": "is_admin=true só é válido com position=Gestor -> 400 (.refine do Zod)."
      }
    }
  ]
}
